name: Natural gas, at extraction site
description:
Natural gas is commonly co-extracted with crude oil. However, there are enough differences between crude oil and natural gas extraction to merit separate data modules for each product., 
Important note: although most of the data in the US LCI database has 
undergone some sort of review, the database as a whole has not yet 
undergone a formal validation process.
Please email comments to lci@nrel.gov.

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Includes data for natural gas extracted from onshore and offshore wells. Includes data for natural gas co-extracted with crude oil as well as for wells that produced only natural gas.
processDocumentation.restrictionsDescription: All information can be accessed by everybody.
